data.title: Commanding General, United States Army Forces Command
data.meta_description: The Commanding General of United States Army Forces Command is the head of United States Army Forces Command (FORSCOM). In this position, he or she is in charge of approximately 780,000 Active Army, U.S. Army Reserve, and Army National Guard soldiers – 87 percent of the Army's combat power.
